# FragranceDNA Environment Variables

## Authentication Configuration

### Email/Password Authentication
# No environment variables required for basic email/password auth
# Uses localStorage for session management (development only)

### Google OAuth 2.0 Configuration
# Get these from Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/

# OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application)
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here

# OAuth 2.0 Client Secret (keep this private, use in .env.local only)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret_here

# Google OAuth Redirect URI (must match console configuration)
GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/auth/callback/google

### Apple Sign In Configuration
# Get these from Apple Developer: https://developer.apple.com/

# Apple Service ID (Bundle ID format)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APPLE_SERVICE_ID=com.fragrance-dna.web

# Apple Team ID
APPLE_TEAM_ID=your_apple_team_id

# Apple Key ID
APPLE_KEY_ID=your_apple_key_id

# Apple Private Key (keep this private)
APPLE_PRIVATE_KEY=your_apple_private_key_here

# Apple OAuth Redirect URI
APPLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/auth/callback/apple

## Production Deployment

# Vercel Environment
NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_URL=https://fragrance-dna.vercel.app

# Update OAuth redirect URIs for production:
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://fragrance-dna.vercel.app/auth/callback/google
# APPLE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://fragrance-dna.vercel.app/auth/callback/apple

## Development Notes

### Setting Up Google OAuth:
1. Create a Google Cloud project
2. Enable Google+ API
3. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (Web Application)
4. Add localhost:3000 and localhost:3000/auth/callback/google to authorized redirect URIs
5. Copy Client ID to NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
6. Copy Client Secret to GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET

### Setting Up Apple Sign In:
1. Create an Apple Developer account
2. Register your app and domain
3. Create a Service ID
4. Generate a private key
5. Copy values to corresponding environment variables

### Local Development:
- Copy this file to .env.local
- Replace placeholders with actual values
- Never commit .env.local to version control
- Use email/password authentication during development if OAuth setup is not ready

### Testing Authentication:
- Email sign-in: Use any email and password (min 8 chars)
- Google OAuth: Simulated locally, uses mock user data
- Apple OAuth: Simulated locally, uses mock user data
- Session: Persisted in localStorage (cleared on sign-out)
